data.title: The Hashemites

data.text:
Ahlan wa Sahlan! Here is your daily dose of the Jordanian royal family and the beautiful country located in the heart of the Middle East.

Disclaimer: Please read my FAQ page before asking. Repetitive asks will not be answered. The blog owner answers most questions in a direct manner, so this blog is not glass-hearted-friendly. Moreover, this is not a fan blog but information hub for the family. None of the photos belongs to me unless otherwise stated. Pictures will be promptly removed if you're the original owner.

Princess Firyal on her late ex-husband, 7 May 2021

بعد مرور اسبوع اليم على رحيل صاحب السمو الامير محمد بن طلال بن عبدالله الاول الهاشمي، ابو طلال الغالي، واني ساذكر دوما بعطف وحنان والشكر والامتنان للسنين العديده والحياه المشتركه وهبه الله لنا باولادنا طلال وغازي، سائلين الله عز وجل رحمته وان يسكنه فسيح جنانه.

After the passing of the good week after the departure of His Highness Prince Muhammad bin Talal bin Abdullah Al-Awal Al-Hashemi, Abu Talal Al-Ghali, and I will always remember with sympathy, tenderness, thanks and gratitude for the many years and the common life that God has gifted us with our children Talal and Ghazi, asking God Almighty for his mercy and that he dwell in his spaciousness.
